Interface Tree

All Superinterfaces:
Serializable
All Known Subinterfaces:
MutableTree
All Known Implementing Classes:
BaseMutableTree, BaseTree
public interface Tree
extends Serializable

This interface defines a tree that can be used to manage objects spatially. Objects that are inserted into this tree can be located quickly using one of several search() methods. Only objects of type SpatialNode can be added to the tree. A typical use for this object is to first populate the tree using insert() then to query the tree using one of the various search() methods.

Spatial objects that have been added to this tree cannot be removed from the tree. For this reason, the tree is considered to be "immutable" even though insert() is provided.
